  <description><![CDATA[<ul>
<li>Resort altitude: 1,579 metres</li>
<li>180 km of skiing</li>
<li>11 Blue, 33 Red, 9 Black runs</li>
<li><span>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 45 mins from Turin airport by coach</span></li>
</ul>
<p>Without a doubt, Champoluc is the most popular resort in the hidden gem that is the Monterosa ski area in <a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy">Italy</a>. This is a haven for those who are looking to take their skiing and snowboarding off the beaten path in an authentic Italian setting. There’s a good range of shops, bars and patisseries to enjoy as well as the Monterosa spa located at the top end of town next to the woodland park, perfect if you need a day’s rest and fancy a bit of pampering.</p>
<h2>Skiing and snowboarding in Champoluc</h2>
<p>The ski area continues to surprise even the most competent skiers and boarders every year for many reasons. Not only are the pistes extremely well maintained but majority of the season they feel empty compared to the busy slopes in neighbouring countries.</p>
<p>You have three extensive ski areas which are covered with one lift pass; Champoluc, <a data-udi="umb://document/df8adba64dd44f3c87eb2df1c821a98e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/df8adba64dd44f3c87eb2df1c821a98e}" title="Gressoney">Gressoney</a> and Alagna which are linked by a modern lift system throughout the valleys.</p>
<p>The majority of the slopes are aimed towards intermediate and advanced skiers but the real star of the show is the mass of off-piste areas. True powder hunters will want to head towards the Punta Indren lift and hit up the un-pisted terrain, just make sure you have the correct equipment as it’s not for the faint hearted.</p>
<p><strong>Prebookable ski guiding</strong></p>
<p>Enjoy a stress-free tour of the local ski area and get your bearings on the first morning of your holiday with a local qualified guide. Get insight into the best runs and places to ski on the mountain as well as some useful pointers along the way to improve technique.</p>
<p><strong>Free ski away day</strong></p>
<p>Sign up to our free ski away day, available to all our guests staying in Champoluc who have pre-booked a lift pass. Our in-resort team will take you to another Aosta Valley resort such as Cervinia, where you can spend the day exploring before jumping on the Inghams coach back to Champoluc. </p>
<h2>Where to stay in Champoluc</h2>
<p>Like all of the villages in the area, Champoluc is filled with rustic charm and is beautiful to explore, especially as you follow the walkway alongside the river which flows all the way through the village. </p>
<p>We have a great range of accommodation on offer here from the <a data-udi="umb://document/6bfba831952648e4914c5b747bee97f3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6bfba831952648e4914c5b747bee97f3}" title="Hotel De Champoluc">Hotel De Champoluc</a> with doorstep skiing to excellent 3-5* hotels.</p>
<h2>Bars and restaurants in Champoluc</h2>
<p>At the weekend, Champoluc is a popular destination with the Italian locals who travel up from Milan and Turin, and the whole resort comes to life with après culture.</p>
<p>As you come off the mountain the home run is next to the ski hire shop, so you can drop off your skis and join in the fun.</p>
<h2>What's included in an Inghams holiday to<span> </span><span>Champoluc</span></h2>
<p>Flights, transfers and accommodation based on bed and breakfast or half board. Optional add ons include equipment hire, lift pass and tuition, please see the 'Ski extras' tab below for more information on these.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">You might also like</span></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda}" title="Cervinia"><span>Discover Cervinia ski holidays</span></a></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/44c205035969462abff34bd958a9f9af" href="/{localLink:umb://document/44c205035969462abff34bd958a9f9af}" title="Aosta Valley Ski Area"><span>Discover more Aosta Valley ski holidays</span></a></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy"><span>Discover more Italy holidays</span></a></p>]]></description>
