  <tagline><![CDATA[A unspoilt village in the snow-sure Monterosa ski area, one of the largest ski areas in Italy.]]></tagline>
  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; color: #023761;"><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #023761;">Food &amp; Drink</span></p>
<p>Champoluc offers some fabulous authentic Italian restaurants serving classic and contemporary food. One of the great things about the Monterosa ski area is that the lovely food isn’t restricted to the town of Champoluc; the mountain restaurants are also delicious and serve unique a la carte menus. You’ll find bars with live music, delicious wines and cocktails, but the atmosphere remains a lot calmer and more relaxed than other alpine resorts.</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; color: #023761;"><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #023761;">Shopping</span></p>
<p>Champoluc offers the usual sporting goods stores, a few souvenir shops and one supermarket in the small village. Please note: there is no weekly market. If you are interested in a shopping trip, then a day excursion to the nearby cities of Milan and Turin, or even the nearby town of Aosta is bound to be more successful. Popular souvenirs to take back home include hand-carved wooden clogs!</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; color: #023761;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">Spa &amp; Relaxation</span></p>
<p>The MonterosaSPA is the perfect place to relax after a day on the slopes. There are a range of different pools, steam rooms and saunas to enjoy as well as various treatments and massages available. To visit the spa, you need to book in advance - this is best to organise by asking the staff in your hotel. To get there walk up through the centre of town, past the main ski lift heading up towards Frachey and you will find it situated on the left next to the pharmacy.</p>]]></thingsToDo>
